main event: On 25th January 1958 at 7:30 a.m. in Levittown, New York, a military source reported observing 5 unidentified flying objects for about 10 minutes, capturing them in a photograph. Analysis of the film was inconclusive and the objects exhibited erratic behavior. The witnesses observed the objects emitting a bright light and moving at low altitude, displaying swift, vertical motion and a lack of sound.
